item.title: Overloadx || eco || Custom items || Vps || Webhost || Need Staff
item.dc:creator: @sour sour
item.description:
@sour wrote:

Lets face it, just because you found OverloadX to be fun and entertaining doesn’t mean the rest of us will. We all have different likes/dislikes when it comes to Private Servers. It seems that most people these days enjoy the 700+ revision(s). However, there are a few people out there that like older-styled servers, like myself. Point is, OverloadX was a thing of the past. Do you even know why the owner shut it down? Possibly because it was dieing?

Moving on. If you even want to consider gaining players, I suggest you actually ‘change’ the server around a bit. If anyone happened to play OverloadX in the past, they wouldn’t want to play it again with the exact same features and such, would they? I also suggest you work on a forum. Forums help your players stay up-to-date with the daily updates and whatnot, it’s the main form of communication between staff and players. With this being said, best of luck to you, mate.
